This paper proposes a new reinforcement learning algorithm that focuses on robustness, which is a common concern in machine learning. The paper also introduces a novel min-max game formulation and a zero-order optimization method. These topics are all related to machine learning and optimization, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories as they cover a broad range of topics related to machine learning and reinforcement learning. cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also relevant as the paper focuses on control tasks. Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely category, but it is still possible as the paper mentions high-dimensional MuJuCo environments, which could involve computer vision techniques.
